The paper deals with information retrieval, which is a core topic in computer science. The focus is on retrieving documents that describe sequences of events, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task falling under the sub-category of cs.CL. The paper proposes an action language-based formalization, which is a type of logic programming, falling under the sub-category of cs.AI. The paper also mentions the use of Answer Set Programming, which is a declarative programming paradigm, falling under the sub-category of cs.SE. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of matching documents and queries, which is a machine learning task, falling under the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.IR.
